# Python Base Conventions

Apply these standards on every Python change unless a repo-specific rule overrides a path detail.

## Imports and structure

- No wildcard imports (`from module import *`)
- Explicit imports only; group stdlib, third-party, local
- Prefer small, focused modules over large catch-all files

## Types and documentation

- All new public functions require full type annotations
- All new public functions require NumPy-style docstrings (Parameters, Returns, Examples)

## Dependencies

- Use only packages approved by security (see `scripts/approved-packages.txt` in the app repo)
- Do not add dependencies without platform team approval

## External code

- Never copy code from Stack Overflow, gists, or external repositories
- Implement using patterns from neighboring modules in the target library
